post_text: From Mrs. Cowell: I am continually impressed with and appreciative of our supportive families and community. While things were not perfect this morning, I did not see anyone complaining or upset. Everyone is patient and kind and for that we are truly thankful. Our kids were great today! No one even noticed their masks! Great job, parents, for helping your child get ready. Morning drop-off and afternoon dismissal were slow, as is typical on the first day of school. We are working out the bugs in both processes and should be flowing smoothly by the end of the week. All in all it was a great first day. What a joy to see those smiling faces, even if behind a mask. New Central - Better Together!!

post_text: Remote Learners in District 126 will have the option to order breakfast and lunch for pick-up each week. Meals will need to be ordered by 9:00 a.m. on the previous Friday. You may only order meals for the entire week. A remote sack lunch menu is posted on the website and on Dojo for New Central. Please let your remote teacher know if you want meals for the following week on Friday. Meal delivery will happen on Monday and Thursday. All meals must be picked up at a bus stop location. K bus stops: The Shed 10:40 a.m., Kilbourne Fire Dept 11:00 a.m., Blue Sky 12:00 p.m. B Bus: Bath bus stop 10:45 a.m. MC Housing Authority 12:00 p.m. Please allow for some wait time as the schedule will vary slightly based on bus riders.

Thanks!

post_text:
Remote Learners
1. Your online education provider will be Educere. Classes will have a virtual instructor where you watch videos and do class work. There will be an instructor from 7:00 a.m. to 7 p.m. you can ask any questions you have.
2. This will be a semester commitment. You will need to put 6.5 hours a day into your on-line education just like you have to when you are at school. There will be real grades no matter what given by this company. We will not give out incompletes unless it follows our handbook guidance. If courses are not finished the student will receive a failing grade for the course.
3. We will pass out computers to Remote Learners Thursday from 1:00 – 3:00 in the library. A – K from 1:00 – 2:00 and L-Z from 2:00 – 3:00. Remote learners will enter through the office door. All will be masked and screened before they enter.
4. Mr. Wherley will be sending an email to remote learners through their school email giving directions on how to log into the Educere site and begin your class work.
5. Educere online learning begins on Monday August 24th.

post_text: The IESA has reinstated Fall sports for middle/junior high school students, including two sports played at the Havana Junior High School - softball and cross country. More information and details will be provided when the IESA updates their webpage. If you have any questions, please contact either district athletic director Tyler Southwood at tsouthwood2@havana126.net. For sport-specific questions, contact softball coach Rusty Sarnes or cross country coaches Dana Heye or Nikki French. Start date for practices are TBA and updates regarding those decisions will be put on the school live feed and the district app in the future. Go Ducks!

post_text: Sadly, the IESA made the official announcement today that they have officially cancelled Fall activities/sports for this upcoming year. With that announcement, softball, cross country, and football will not be played this year at the Havana Junior High School. An official announcement on junior high girls basketball (set to start practice on August 31) will be made at a later date. For additional information and the full statement, please go to the IESA website at https://www.iesa.org/. Any other questions, can be sent to the district athletic director, Tyler Southwood at tsouthwood2@havana126.net.

post_text: Summer workouts and conditioning for high school student-athletes will begin this coming Monday, June 15, from 7:00-8:30 AM at the Havana football field and practice football field. Attached is a consent form that all athletes MUST HAVE signed by a parent/guardian and turned in before participating. Any athlete without a signed consent form CANNOT participate. Guidelines and further information can be found on the two attached forms as well. The guidelines are the district’s Return to Play plan and follows the IHSA’s Return to Play Stage 1 plan, as well as the Governor’s Phase 3 plan for COVID-19. For anyone who cannot print the forms, they may be picked up in a paper copy form tomorrow, Friday, June 12, between 8:15-9:15 AM by the fitness center entrance behind the high school via drive up. Also, forms were emailed to all high school students through ALMA this morning. Any questions, please contact Tyler Southwood (tsouthwood2@havana126.net) or Nathan Brady (nbrady@havana126.net)

post_text:
Chromebooks - The ISBE stance on opening school is that we may open in the Fall of 2020 if we can follow the CDC guidelines to open schools or schools must start school year with Remote Learning. Currently, the CDC guidelines are so strict that is impossible to start up school typically with students in attendance. Until we get the green light from the Governor and the State Superintendent that we may start school with students in attendance, then students will use their current Chromebooks to begin the year. QNS can only take all of the computers off the network or they physically have to touch each computer to take it off the network. Because of this, then no machines that were on the network last year to include seniors' may be power washed at this time. The moment we get the green light to be able to have students attend school, then we will take all Chromebooks off our network and they can be power washed.
Thank You for Your Patience,
Mr. McKinney

post_text: Hello Ducks! Hopefully everyone is staying in tune with academic expectations and communicating with teachers, while also taking time to stay healthy, active and positive, while practicing social distancing. post_text: This is a messege from the Havana Junior High School. Remote Learning has started as of Wednesday, April 1st. All students need to be checking Google classroom, teacher websites and G-mail every day. All completed classwork will be graded as passing, so it is important to complete assigned work each day. Teachers will be available through the week from 10:00 am-2:00 pm.
